# Sprint 52.hotfix.a (2026-05-17, Item 156) — explicit .html rewrites for
# Next.js carrier routes. Pre-fix `/carrier/* /carrier/:splat 200` echoed
# :splat as identity rewrite target; Cloudflare Pages then resolved the
# extensionless path ambiguously between out/carrier/<name>.html and
# out/carrier/<name>.txt (Next.js static export generates BOTH siblings —
# .html for browser navigation, .txt for client-side RSC streaming).
# Gmail iOS WebView Accept-header content negotiation landed on the .txt
# RSC payload, displaying raw "1:$Sreact.fragment" Flight payload instead
# of the rendered carrier login page. Fix: enumerate Next.js routes with
# explicit .html rewrites; deterministic resolution; matches /verify/* +
# /track/* single-target precedent intent. Legacy static HTML in
# public/carrier/ (analytics, help, loads, register, tools, etc.) resolves
# via Cloudflare default extension fallback — no rule needed because no
# .txt sibling exists for those files.
/carrier/login            /carrier/login.html             200
/carrier/forgot-password  /carrier/forgot-password.html   200
/carrier/reset-password   /carrier/reset-password.html    200
/carrier/dashboard        /carrier/dashboard.html         200
/carrier/dashboard/*      /carrier/dashboard/:splat.html  200

